    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "A total of 80 bridges are expected to be built during the phase and the programme will have mainly four components:\r\ni) Construction and piloting of new bridges (having average span of 40 meters to support loads of 15 tonnes on average) and approaches corresponding to outputs 1, 2 & 3\r\nii) Generation of knowledge and technological transfers corresponding to output 4\r\niii) Formulation of policy, strategies, business plans, norms and standards corresponding to output 4\r\niv) Capacity building of GoN, local communities and private sector[1] corresponding to output \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[1] Out of 1200 registered private contractors of different class categories (A,B,C and D), very few A and B class contractors have \r\nexperience on building road bridges at a standard prescribed by DoR."
      },
